citations:
    citation-affc-jaime-iv:
        source: source-affc
        properties:
            locator: "Jaime IV"
            text_from_source: "The trumpets made a brazen blare, and cut the still blue air of dusk."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Jaime arrives at the siege of Riverrun and meets his cousin Ser Daven Lannister (Warden of the West). He learns the state of the siege: the Blackfish has expelled useless mouths and provisioned the castle for two years; Ser Ryman Frey daily threatens to hang Edmure Tully but always relents; Aunt Genna Lannister and her husband Lord Emmon Frey are camped outside. Jaime also learns that Robb Stark's queen Jeyne Westerling is inside the castle with the Blackfish. He consults with Genna and Emmon about the siege."
